  "texts": [
    "The method of selecting the appropriate algorithm to establish data correlations is one of the hot topics of research.",
    "[19,[217][218][219][220][221][222][223][224][225][226].",
    "Sandeep and Natarajan [227] used the optimal linear associative memory (OLAM) neural network to establish the data association between cutting parameters, spindle motor load, and tool wear status in the turning process, and the correct rate reached 93.8%.",
    "Lei et al. [166] studied three kernel-based supervised learning algorithms and monitored the medium wear rate during the grinding process using solid percentage, mill speed, and grinding time as input factors.",
    "Lee et al. [165] used deep learning methods to establish a data correlation between the frequency domain signals of sound during machining and the wear status of grinding wheels, thereby monitor the tool status during grinding."
  ],
